{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_popups_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-10-show-readonly-ex-output-popups/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_popups_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-10-show-readonly-ex-output-popups/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "pi-vimmode currently has two read-only output paths for Ex help and diagnostics: - Most read-only commands (`:help`, `:features` except keybinding discovery, `:actions`, `:keymap`, `:mapcheck`, `:messages`, `:vimmode inspect`, `:vimdoctor`) exit Ex command-line mode and place a compact informational message in the existing workbench/message row."}, {"id": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_popups_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-10-show-readonly-ex-output-popups/design.md", "source_location": "line 19", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Provide one reusable popup UI for all valid read-only Ex help/diagnostic outputs listed in the proposal."}, {"id": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_popups_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-10-show-readonly-ex-output-popups/design.md", "source_location": "line 39", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "### Decision 1: Generalize popup data and component instead of adding more inline rows **Target seams:** `src/keybinding-discovery-popup.ts`, `src/keybinding-discovery-overlay.ts`, `src/modal/types.ts`, `src/vim-editor.ts`."}, {"id": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_popups_design_decision_1_generalize_popup_data_and_component_instead_of_adding_more_inline_rows", "label": "Decision 1: Generalize popup data and component instead of adding more inline rows", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-10-show-readonly-ex-output-popups/design.md", "source_location": "line 41", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Target seams:** `src/keybinding-discovery-popup.ts`, `src/keybinding-discovery-overlay.ts`, `src/modal/types.ts`, `src/vim-editor.ts`. Create a generic read-only popup model such as `ExHelpPopup` with fields for title, lines, source command/category, docs anchor, and scroll offset. Rename or wrap the current keybinding-specific builder/component into a reusable `ExHelpOverlayComponent`. Keep keybinding discovery as one content builder that produces the generic model."}, {"id": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_popups_design_decision_2_route_valid_read_only_command_results_through_one_modal_popup_effect", "label": "Decision 2: Route valid read-only command results through one modal popup effect", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-10-show-readonly-ex-output-popups/design.md", "source_location": "line 53", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Target seams:** `src/modal/ex-command-line.ts`, `src/modal/types.ts`, `src/vim-editor.ts`. Add or rename a modal effect such as `openReadOnlyPopup` / `openHelpPopup` that carries the generic popup model. `executeExCommand` should convert successful parsed read-only commands into popup content after applying the existing source-mode restoration logic. `VimEditor` remains the only layer that calls `tui.showOverlay()`."}, {"id": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_popups_design_decision_3_preserve_compact_workbench_feedback_for_edit_flows_parser_errors_and_noh", "label": "Decision 3: Preserve compact workbench feedback for edit flows, parser errors, and :noh", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-10-show-readonly-ex-output-popups/design.md", "source_location": "line 71", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Target seams:** `src/modal/ex-command-line.ts`, `src/vim-editor.ts`, `src/render.ts`. Only valid read-only help/diagnostic command output moves to popup. Mutating/editing Ex commands continue to produce edit effects and compact success/error feedback. Parser errors and unsupported command errors remain transient Ex/workbench messages because they are short command-line feedback, not read-only help content. `:noh` remains a compact no-op-style Ex command because it clears search highlights and "}, {"id": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_popups_design_decision_4_popup_content_uses_existing_source_backed_message_builders_split_into_bounded_lines", "label": "Decision 4: Popup content uses existing source-backed message builders, split into bounded lines", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-10-show-readonly-ex-output-popups/design.md", "source_location": "line 82", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Target seams:** `src/runtime-help.ts`, `src/customization.ts`, `src/diagnostic-actions.ts`, `src/modal/inspect.ts`, docs-drift tests. Do not create a second source-of-truth registry for popup content. Reuse current source-backed runtime help entries, diagnostic action metadata, customization messages, and inspectability summaries, but expose popup-friendly line arrays/title metadata. Existing compact messages may remain as formatting helpers or fallback text, but docs/spec/test anchors must va"}, {"id": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_popups_design_decision_5_popup_local_controls_stay_inside_overlay_component", "label": "Decision 5: Popup-local controls stay inside overlay component", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-10-show-readonly-ex-output-popups/design.md", "source_location": "line 93", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Target seams:** generic overlay component and live `VimEditor` overlay tests. The overlay component owns read-only input handling:"}, {"id": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_popups_design_decision_6_small_terminal_behavior_is_explicit_and_bounded", "label": "Decision 6: Small-terminal behavior is explicit and bounded", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-10-show-readonly-ex-output-popups/design.md", "source_location": "line 110", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Target seams:** `src/vim-editor.ts`, overlay options, live editor tests. For supported terminal sizes, read-only command output opens the centered overlay. If the terminal cannot satisfy the minimum viable overlay viewport, the adapter should use a bounded fallback that does not edit prompt text or lose state, such as a compact transient message telling the user the terminal is too small for the popup. This fallback is a last-resort accessibility/visibility guard, not the normal display path."}, {"id": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_popups_design_risks_trade_offs", "label": "Risks / Trade-offs", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-10-show-readonly-ex-output-popups/design.md", "source_location": "line 121", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- **Message-history pollution** \u2192 Popup display, scroll, and dismissal must not append popup content to `messageHistory`. Preserve `:messages` special behavior where the output itself is not retained. - **Visual source-mode regression** \u2192 Reuse existing `restoreVisualExState` behavior before opening popup and add live tests from visual mode for representative commands. - **Naming drift from keybinding-specific types** \u2192 Rename generic model/effect/component or clearly separate generic fields fro"}, {"id": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_popups_design_ref_src_ex_ts", "label": "ex.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-10-show-readonly-ex-output-popups/design.md", "source_location": "line 13", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_popups_design_ref_src_config_ts", "label": "config.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-10-show-readonly-ex-output-popups/design.md", "source_location": "line 16", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_popups_design_ref_src_types_ts", "label": "types.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-10-show-readonly-ex-output-popups/design.md", "source_location": "line 16", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_popups_design_ref_docs_features_md", "label": "features.md", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-10-show-readonly-ex-output-popups/design.md", "source_location": "line 17", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_popups_design_ref_src_keybinding_discovery_popup_ts", "label": "keybinding-discovery-popup.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-10-show-readonly-ex-output-popups/design.md", "source_location": "line 43", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "2026_06_10_show_readonly_ex_output_po